passes.benefit_text:
This pass admits up to 4 people for free . Children under 6 are always admitted for free .&nbsp;
This is a physical pass that must be picked up at and returned to the library .&nbsp;
This pass is not limited by date or time .&nbsp;
This pass can be used for special programs , provided the program is being held on-site during the Museum's regular operating hours .

This pass admits up to 4&nbsp; people (adults or children) at half price per person.
This is an e-ticket &nbsp;which does not need &nbsp; to be picked up at the library .&nbsp;
This pass is only valid for use &nbsp;on the date for which you reserve it.&nbsp;
You must reserve your visit &nbsp;on the museum's website after receiving the pass .&nbsp;
This pass is funded by the Friends of the Stoneham Library.

The coupon code covers the cost of up to 12 tickets per mainstage show. There is a limit of 2 tickets per person.
This pass is NOT a reservation and does not need to be picked up at the library. You must reserve a ticket for a specific day and time prior to the performance you wish to attend. Tickets must be reserved by calling the Greater Boston Stage Company at&nbsp;(781) 279-2200. The GBSC Box Office is open noon to 4 pm Tuesday through Friday. Your tickets are only valid for the date and time you reserve.
This season's Main Stage shows:
Featherbaby opens on Friday, September 12th and runs through Sunday, December 28th. &nbsp;
Murder for Two opens on Friday, October 5th and runs through Sunday, November 9th.&nbsp;
An Irish Carol opens on Friday, December 5th and runs through Sunday, December 21st.&nbsp;

No pass is needed. Present your physical or digital Massachusetts library card at the Admissions Desk to receive a 50% discount on the cardholder's admission ticket. This offer is valid for visitors aged 13 and over and the visitor must present a Massachusetts library card to receive the discount.&nbsp;
Visitors aged 12 and under receive free admission. Please reach out to the JFK Library Visitor Services Department with questions at kennedy.groupvisits@nara.gov or 617-514-1600.
Need a library card? Visit our website&nbsp;to learn more.

This pass admits one car for free parking at any Massachusetts State Park. See a list of Massachusetts State Parks here .&nbsp;
This is a physical pass which must be picked up at and returned to the library .&nbsp;
This pass is valid for use on any day/time until the date printed on the pass .&nbsp;

This is a physical pass and must be picked up from and returned to the library .
This pass is valid for regular on-site rentals at all locations during regular hours of operation during the boating season (the first weekend in May through mid-October, weather permitting).&nbsp;
This pass is not valid for Fourth of July Fireworks Rentals or any other special event or activity .&nbsp;
Hours of Operation and Directions:
Stoneham: Spot Pond &nbsp;(closed weekdays after Labor Day)
Boston: Allston/Brighton

This pass admits up to 2 adults at a discount rate of $12 per person . Children age 16 and under are free .&nbsp;
This pass is an e-voucher that does not need to be picked up at or returned to the library .&nbsp;
You must book a date and time for your visit after you have reserved the pass . You can do so by visiting the PEM website or by calling (978) 542-1511 . On the PEM ticket page, enter the unique promo code you received upon reserving the pass, and then select your discounted admission tickets. Timed tickets to Yin Yu Tang: A Chinese Home are included with museum admission and may be selected as part of the online checkout process.&nbsp;

This pass admits up to 6 people at a discounted rate of $14.00 for adults or seniors , $11.75 for children 3-14 .&nbsp;
This is a physical pass that must be picked up at and returned to the library .&nbsp;
Present the pass at the ticket booth for discounted admission.&nbsp;
Passes are not accepted in the month of October.

This pass admits up to 2 adults and 2 children under 18 &nbsp;at an equivalent to a Trustees Family Membership admission price at Trustees properties that charge and admission fee. This pass is valid for admission only; it is not valid for discounts at parking kiosks, stores, cafes, inns, campgrounds, at special events or programs, on equipment rentals, or in place of any permits or passes.&nbsp;
This is a physical pass that must be picked up at the library and can be discarded after use .&nbsp;
This pass is not limited by date or time .&nbsp;
This pass is valid at any of 100+ Trustees properties . Hours vary by location. To see a list of Trustees properties, click here. &nbsp;

This pass admits up to 6 people for a discounted rate of $9.00 for adults and $6.00 for children .&nbsp;
This is a physical pass that must be picked up at the library and can be discarded after use .&nbsp;
This pass is not limited by date or time , but can only be used once .&nbsp;
This pass offers admission to either the Stone Zoo or the Franklin Park Zoo .&nbsp;
